  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by seeking to repay the embezzled funds. While the breach of trust is serious, a 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is disproportionate to the amount stolen. A moderate custodial sentence serves as a deterrent while acknowledging the defendant's lack of a criminal record and the partial restitution made.",
  "verdict": 8
